modules.description: This module implements binary decision diagrams (BDDs) for efficient manipulation of Boolean functions. It supports operations like negation, conjunction, disjunction, and variable creation, along with structural inspection and custom printing of BDDs. Typical use cases include formal verification tasks, symbolic model checking, and automated reasoning over Boolean expressions.

This module implements binary decision diagrams (BDDs) for efficient manipulation of Boolean functions. It provides operations for creating, composing, and evaluating BDDs, including conjunction, disjunction, negation, and variable quantification. Typical use cases include formal verification, logic synthesis, and solving combinatorial problems using symbolic representations.
